<author><name><![CDATA[James]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-08-18T16:54:35-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-08-18T16:54:35-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10344&amp;p=116691#p116691</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10344&amp;p=116691#p116691"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Anyone has a real NTSC Incredible Crash Test Dummies car]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10344&amp;p=116691#p116691"><![CDATA[
IRQ is being asserted on the falling edge of A12 instead of the rising edge, so it occurs 4 PPU cycles later compared to MMC3.<br /><br /><img src="http://nemulator.com/images/MC-ACC_IRQ.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I've implemented this behavior in my emulator and the game is working correctly now.  Oh, and I did see the garbage on the right hand side of the screen while testing.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=88">James</a> — Sun Aug 18, 2013 4:54 pm</p><hr />
